<REFENTRY id="hostname">
<REFMETA><REFENTRYTITLE>hostname</REFENTRYTITLE></REFMETA>

<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>hostname</REFNAME>

<REFPURPOSE>
show or set the system's host name
</REFPURPOSE>

</REFNAMEDIV>

<REFSYNOPSISDIV>
<CMDSYNOPSIS>
<COMMAND>hostname</COMMAND>
<ARG>name</ARG>
</CMDSYNOPSIS>
</REFSYNOPSISDIV>


<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Description</TITLE>
<PARA>
<COMMAND>hostname</COMMAND> is used to either display or, with appropriate
privileges, set the current host
name of the system.  The host name is used by many applications
to identify the machine. 
</PARA>

<PARA>
When called without any arguments, the program displays the name of
the system as returned by the <FUNCTION>gethostname</FUNCTION> function.
</PARA>

<PARA>
When called with a <PARAMETER>name</PARAMETER> argument, and the user has appropriate
privilege, the command
sets the host name.
</PARA>

</REFSECT1>

</REFENTRY>
